y.','3 hours.'),(10128,'MUSIC',3696,'A/B','ELECTROACOUSTIC MUSIC COMPOSITION','Course DescriptionContinued study of the terminology and technology of electronic music. Historical development, musique concrète, the “classical” studio, the synthesizer, and computer applications. Survey of the literature with some analysis. Compositional techniques and notation peculiar to electronic music and its real-time performance.','3 hours.'),(10129,'MUSIC',3700,'A/B','TOPICS IN MEDIEVAL MUSIC','Course DescriptionSelected topics in the historical, cultural, and analytical study of medieval music (c. 900 - 1400).','3 hours.'),(10130,'MUSIC',3701,'A/B','TOPICS IN RENAISSANCE MUSIC','Course DescriptionSelected topics in the historical, cultural, and analytical study of Renaissance music (c. 1400 - 1600).','3 hours.'),(10131,'MUSIC',3702,'A/B','TOPICS IN BAROQUE MUSIC','Course DescriptionSelected topics in the historical, cultural, and analytical study of Baroque music (c. 1600 - 1750).','3 hours.'),(10132,'MUSIC',3703,'A/B','TOPICS IN CLASSICAL MUSIC','Course DescriptionSelected topics in the historical, cultural, and analytical study of Classical music (c. 1750 - 1810).','3 hours'),(10133,'MUSIC',3704,'A/B','TOPICS IN ROMANTIC MUSIC','Course DescriptionSelected topics in the historical, cultural, and analytical study of Romantic music (c. 1800 - 1900).','3 hours.'),(10134,'MUSIC',3705,'A/B','TOPICS IN EARLY TWENTIETH CENTURY MUSIC','Course DescriptionSelected topics in the historical, cultural, and analytical study of music c. 1900 to 1950.','3 hours.'),(10135,'MUSIC',3706,'A/B','TOPICS IN LATE 20TH CENTURY MUSIC','Course DescriptionSelected topics in the historical , cultural, and analytical study of music c. 1950 to the present.','3 hours.'),(10136,'MUSIC',3710,'A/B','ISSUES IN PERFORMANCE PRACTICES I','Course DescriptionA consideration of issues bearing on the performance of music composed before c. 1750.','3 hours.'),(10137,'MUSIC',3711,'A/B','ISSUES IN PERFORMING PRACTICES II','Course DescriptionA consideration of issues bearing on the performance of music composed after c. 1750.','3 hours.'),(10138,'MUSIC',3712,'A/B','BEL CANTO FROM HANDEL TO ROSSINI','Course DescriptionA practical study of the principles of bel canto between c. 1750 and c. 1830 in the music of Handel, Mozart, Rossini, and others. Topics include phrasing, ornamentation, register, legato, staccato, messa di voce, tempo rubato, accent and emphasis, recitative and air.','1 lecture hour, 2 laboratory hours (practicum).'),(10139,'MUSIC',3713,'A/B','TOPICS IN ETHNOMUSICOLOGY','Course DescriptionSelected topics in ethnomusicology - the study of musical traditions in their cultural and social contexts.','3 hours.'),(10140,'MUSIC',3730,'A/B','POPULAR MUSIC: GENRE STUDIES','Course DescriptionDetailed study of one or more genres in popular music. Emphasis on repertory, style, and historical context.','3 hours.'),(10141,'MUSIC',3732,'F/G','HITTING THE RIGHT NOTES: SONG LYRIC WRITING','Course DescriptionAn introduction to the basics of effective lyric writing using a variety of literary tools.','3 hours. Cross-listed withWriting 3402F/G.'),(10142,'MUSIC',3733,'A/B','TOPICS IN JAZZ I','Course DescriptionDetailed study of particular artists, styles, or periods in the history and sociology of jazz.','3 hours.'),(10143,'MUSIC',3734,'A/B','DIGITAL AUDIO RECORDING','Course DescriptionAn introduction to the theory and practice of digitally recording, editing, and mixing acoustic music in ambient spaces with Pro Tools.','3 hours.'),(10144,'MUSIC',3735,'A/B','POPULAR MUSIC SONGWRITING','Course DescriptionIntroduction to the tools and techniques of songwriting in a variety of popular music styles.','3 lecture hours.'),(10145,'MUSIC',3736,'A/B','VOCAL PRE-PRODUCTION, TRACKING, AND EDITING','Course DescriptionPractical acquisition of the fundamental principles essential for preparing pop singers to track and edit vocals.','3 hours (1 lecture hour, 2 lab hours).'),(10146,'MUSIC',3737,'A/B','TOP