ic Performance Studies.','Null'),(10197,'MUSIC',3951,'A/B','SPECIAL TOPICS','Course DescriptionSpecial topics in Music Performance Studies.','3 hours.'),(10198,'MUSIC',3952,'A/B','SPECIAL TOPICS','Course DescriptionSpecial topics in Music Performance Studies.','3 hours.'),(10199,'MUSIC',3953,'A/B','THE HARPSICHORD: PLAYING TECHNIQUE AND ACCOMPANIMENT PRACTICES','Course DescriptionAn introduction to harpsichord technique and playing by means of study of selected solo repertoire, figured bass, and examination of editorial realizations.','3 hours.'),(10200,'MUSIC',3954,'A/B','PERCUSSION ENSEMBLE','Course DescriptionThe rehearsal and performance of a broad range of percussion ensemble repertoire including standard, world, jazz and contemporary styles. Further technical, musical and organization skills building on applied study are explored.','3 hours. Open to Music Students only.'),(10201,'MUSIC',3958,'','PIANO LITERATURE','Course DescriptionA study of the musical literature for solo piano.','3 hours.'),(10202,'MUSIC',3960,'A/B','THE 21ST-CENTURY MUSICIAN','Course DescriptionAn exploration of the classical music industry within the context of the current cultural and economic climate. Topics will include networking, creating a personal portfolio, researching grants and community partnerships, website design, time management, and finances.','3 lecture hours.'),(10203,'MUSIC',3970,'','OPERA WORKSHOP I','Course DescriptionPerforming and technical aspects of the production of opera, including musical and dramatic interpretation, stage movement, techniques of stagecraft, lighting, scene construction, make-up, costumes. An audition is required.','4 hours.'),(10204,'MUSIC',3971,'A','EARLY MUSIC STUDIO','Course DescriptionThe study and performance of repertoire composed before 1800 with attention to historical performance practices. The ensemble performs on period instruments.','Null'),(10205,'MUSIC',3972,'B','EARLY MUSIC STUDIO','Course DescriptionThe study and performance of 